{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017KPfGhYsWhwg2fqcrPPYfx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three criteria are met. Here's a summary of what was done and what was fixed:\n\n**What was configured:**\n\n1. **OpenTelemetry enabled** — patched `ingress-nginx-controller` configmap with `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"`, `otlp-collector-host: \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"`, `otlp-collector-port: \"4317\"`.\n\n2. **100% sampling** — set `otel-sampler: \"AlwaysOn\"`, `otel-sampler-ratio: \"1.0\"`, `otel-sampler-parent-based: \"false\"`.\n\n3. **Log format** — set `log-format-upstream` including `otel_trace_id=$opentelemetry_trace_id otel_span_id=$opentelemetry_span_id`.\n\n**Two decoys fixed:**\n\n- **Wrong configmap key** — the correct key is `otlp-collector-host` (not `opentelemetry-collector-host`); the controller binary uses `OtlpCollectorHost` mapped via `json:\"otlp-collector-host\"`.\n- **Duplicate deployment args** — the deployment had `--controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx-1 --ingress-class=ingress-1` appended at the end, overriding the correct `nginx` class values, causing the controller to ignore all `nginx`-class ingresses including `otel-echo`.\n\n**Verification:**\n\nThe final access log line confirms non-empty IDs:\n```\notel_trace_id=90f3e5000017778e132705e234ff41af otel_span_id=ac78ae7ed57e7551\n```\nAnd the OTel collector received and exported the matching span (`Trace ID: 90f3e5000017778e132705e234ff41af`) from `otel.example.com`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":825,"cache_read_input_tokens":49570,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":825},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d0f8d521-5609-4a96-bd7f-e761df1eda43","uuid":"69d50d1e-2780